The paper discusses a coding scheme for reliable communication over packet networks, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of queueing network models, which falls under the network economics and computation (cs.NE) sub-category. The paper discusses the use of coding for reliable communication, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses both wireline and wireless packet networks, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
